1
00:01:20,620 --> 00:01:22,910
-Enjoy.
-If it's this season…

2
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,540
That goes outside.

3
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:26,660
Got it.

4
00:01:28,450 --> 00:01:29,830
Mulțumesc.

5
00:01:31,450 --> 00:01:32,290
'Neața.

6
00:01:32,370 --> 00:01:35,080
It's also good for storing genomes.

7
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:40,410
SPANISH GRAMMAR

8
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:54,040
MOVING CENTER

9
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:56,500
Thanks for your help.

10
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:40,700
How was the dive yesterday, Tsuneo?

11
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:43,500
I saw a Priolepis nocturna.

12
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,580
Asta e uimitor!

13
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:48,660
I was lucky the sea was so calm.

14
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,950
You're on summer break from college?

15
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:54,370
That's right.

16
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:58,290
How about doing a dive next Wednesday?

17
00:02:58,370 --> 00:02:59,200
Sure!

18
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:02,200
Bring some girls too.

19
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:03,370
Sorry?

20
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:07,330
At this rate, fish will be our only love.

21
00:03:07,410 --> 00:03:10,200
But I long for a human one. Right, Tsuneo?

22
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,120
No time for that.

23
00:03:12,830 --> 00:03:15,450
I start another part-time job next week.

24
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:19,450
You're wasting your youth.

25
00:03:19,540 --> 00:03:22,250
The summer of 22 comes only once.

26
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:24,080
Whatever.

27
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,620
Tsuneo!

28
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,790
Thank you.

29
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:35,790
UNDER CONSTRUCTION

30
00:03:39,450 --> 00:03:41,200
Is this the right way?

31
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:44,120
Help!

32
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:09,540
That hurts.

33
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,410
Are you okay?

34
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:24,000
Kumiko!

35
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:27,250
Kumiko, are you all right?

36
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:37,000
Did you save her, young man? Thank you.

37
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:37,910
No.

38
00:04:38,910 --> 00:04:40,660
Are you injured?

39
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,330
I think I'm fine.

40
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,870
I turn away for one second,
and someone pushes her.

41
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:49,910
I almost had a heart attack.

42
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:53,250
That hurts! Why did you do that?

43
00:04:53,330 --> 00:04:54,370
Pervert.

44
00:04:54,450 --> 00:04:55,290
What?

45
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:58,450
Stop groping me, you pervert!

46
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:08,120
The pervert is following us, Grandma.

47
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:11,120
My house is this way.

48
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,080
Shall I push?

49
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,000
No.

50
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,370
Born this way.

51
00:05:25,870 --> 00:05:28,000
What about our walk, Grandma?

52
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:32,120
We're giving up walks for a while.

53
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,330
I don't want to.

54
00:05:33,410 --> 00:05:37,410
Tough. You can't have everything your way.

55
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:43,330
Do you always take walks at this hour?

56
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:48,910
I thought it'd be safer
and we wouldn't be seen.

57
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:53,120
But the world is full of scary beasts.

58
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,870
Here we are.

59
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,330
I'll be going.

60
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,870
Come on in.

61
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,370
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

62
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,040
Oh, drat.

63
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:24,000
Would octopus dumplings do?

64
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,950
We're out of rice.

65
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:27,450
That's fine.

66
00:06:38,450 --> 00:06:39,830
Not you again.

67
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,500
I keep putting him out but he returns.

68
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:46,620
Don't touch it, Kumiko. It may have fleas.

69
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:47,540
Scat!

70
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:51,250
Just here for some free food.

71
00:06:51,790 --> 00:06:54,000
Do you feed him often?

72
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,540
I meant you.

73
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:01,910
No, he's not a friend. Just a pervert.

74
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:04,370
He understands you.

75
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:06,830
Of course not. Are you stupid?

76
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:12,370
"You're intruding on my territory."

77
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:13,540
That's what he said.

78
00:07:15,290 --> 00:07:16,160
Ms. Kumiko…

79
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:17,410
Josee.

80
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,580
What?

81
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:21,450
I'm not Kumiko. I'm Josee.

82
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,870
Josee?

83
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:33,540
With thanks.

84
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,290
Have seconds.

85
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:48,450
Thank you. I can't afford
to buy another box lunch.

86
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:51,500
You sound very poor. Are you a student?

87
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:55,000
Yes, I rent an apartment nearby.

88
00:07:55,580 --> 00:08:00,200
I'm poor, but I'm also trying
to save money.

89
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:01,830
Nobody's asking.

90
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,120
I'm thirsty, Grandma.

91
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:07,120
Barley tea or water?

92
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,870
-Barley tea.
-Okay.

93
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:11,040
Just a second.

94
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,660
Allow me.

95
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:16,580
It's okay. Don't let your food get cold.

96
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,160
Is this it?

97
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,250
Here.

98
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,870
You're pretty demanding.

99
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:27,410
Ouch, that's hot!

100
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:32,540
What's the deal?

101
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:37,000
Kumiko can't hold onto tea in a cup.

102
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:41,750
How about a plastic bottle? Or a thermos.

103
00:08:42,950 --> 00:08:44,370
You're a funny young man.

104
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:47,950
Thank you for the meal.

105
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:50,120
Sorry for staying so long.

106
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,410
Nonsense. We don't often have guests.

107
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,330
Goodbye.

108
00:08:57,370 --> 00:09:00,080
Do you want to earn some money?

109
00:09:01,950 --> 00:09:03,250
A new job?

110
00:09:03,830 --> 00:09:06,790
Yeah, someone I happened to meet.

111
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,450
It pays really well.

112
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,830
What about this job?

113
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:12,750
I'll continue, of course.

114
00:09:14,540 --> 00:09:17,620
Where's the joy in working so much?

115
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:21,500
I can introduce you too. She's a female.

116
00:09:21,580 --> 00:09:23,040
-Seriously?
-Yes.

117
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,910
About 80 years old.

118
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,160
Figures.

119
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:29,000
Move those hands, Hayato.

120
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,160
Yes, boss.

121
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,910
Have you seen the toolbox?

122
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:38,450
Yeah, the lid needed fixing.

123
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:39,410
Hey, thanks!

124
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:46,040
I might even hire you full-time
when you graduate.

125
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,830
I'll think about it.

126
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:50,750
Not you. I meant Tsuneo Suzukawa here.

127
00:09:51,330 --> 00:09:54,700
I plan to study abroad after college.

128
00:09:55,790 --> 00:10:00,500
Didn't you know, boss?
He's going to the Netherlands.

129
00:10:00,580 --> 00:10:01,830
It's Mexico.

130
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:06,700
Ah, Mexico. I once swam
with a baby sea lion in La Paz.

131
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:11,450
Study abroad, huh?
We're going to miss you.

132
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:14,790
I haven't found a school yet.

133
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:19,950
And he hasn't saved enough.
You should raise his wages.

134
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,580
Mine too, while you're at it.

135
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:23,450
Go check the machines.

136
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:24,910
Right away, sir!

137
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:28,000
What's wrong, Mai?

138
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:33,290
Nothing. Well, tell me
about that job that pays so well.

139
00:10:33,370 --> 00:10:35,910
You are to do as Kumiko says.

140
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:37,700
What?

141
00:10:37,790 --> 00:10:39,580
Didn't I tell you?

142
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:44,000
No, you didn't.
You mean I'd be working here?

143
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:46,700
Yes, you'd be working here.

144
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:51,950
Don't look so disappointed.

145
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:56,580
There's only one rule.
Don't take her out on your own.

146
00:10:57,330 --> 00:10:59,700
Help yourself to anything in the fridge.

147
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:01,830
There's plenty.

148
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:06,000
I have to go.
Kumiko will tell you what to do.

149
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:08,120
Where are you going?

150
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,080
Well… hello.

151
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:22,870
What do I do?

152
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,370
Joan, was it?

153
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:27,330
It's Josee!

154
00:11:32,290 --> 00:11:33,700
-Josee?
-Stay away.

155
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:41,250
"Intruders get out", he says.

156
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:45,120
But I'm working here from today.

157
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:47,950
-Kneel.
-What?

158
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:49,500
On your knees.

159
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,040
Okay, I'm kneeling.

160
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,620
Do you want to live?

161
00:12:00,580 --> 00:12:02,870
Why am I kneeling?

162
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:06,040
To see how long a human can endure it.

163
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,790
Do your job well.

164
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:16,080
I'm going to make her cry.

165
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:20,000
Your look has really changed
in the past month.

166
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:23,330
Is working for this Josee that hard?

167
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:25,500
It's way beyond hard.

168
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,580
Count the meshes in the tatami mats.

169
00:12:28,950 --> 00:12:32,080
It keeps me up at night wondering.

170
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:36,580
5,208, 5,209, 5,210,

171
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:40,160
5,211, 5,212…

172
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,580
Oh, what a waste.

173
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,910
I squandered 8,000 yen
on a bad pachinko machine.

174
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,410
8,001, 8,002, 8,003… Oops.

175
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,950
Start over.

176
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:57,370
Bring me four-leaf clovers.

177
00:12:58,830 --> 00:13:01,370
Four-leaf clovers.

178
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:04,620
Four-leaf clovers…

179
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:06,910
Here.

180
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:09,450
Nothing's happening.

181
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,700
Ten are supposed to grant my wish.

182
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:14,830
Superstition.

183
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:16,750
What wish?

184
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:19,160
Don't speak to me. I'm busy.

185
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:25,290
She looks so meek

186
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:29,290
until she speaks
and becomes a stinging jellyfish.

187
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:33,410
I'd like to glue her
to one of her sliding doors.

188
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,950
Oh, harsh.

189
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:39,830
Why don't you quit?
You need to write your thesis.

190
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:43,200
But I really need the money.

191
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:46,000
You don't have to earn it there.

192
00:13:46,580 --> 00:13:49,450
Even if your hours
at the shop are decreasing.

193
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:52,830
Stop thinking about making a buck

194
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:56,000
and give some attention to Mai.

195
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,250
Eat this and shut up.

196
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,580
Is Tsuneo here?

197
00:14:04,290 --> 00:14:05,120
Professor!

198
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:08,660
There you are. Can you spare a second?

199
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,250
Your essay on Turing Patterns.

200
00:14:13,950 --> 00:14:18,160
I sent it to a professor
at Mexico City University.

201
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:22,160
He loved it and wants you to study there.

202
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:23,450
Thank you!

203
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:27,500
That leaves the question of a scholarship.

204
00:14:27,580 --> 00:14:31,080
It'll be hard to pay your own way.

205
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:33,370
I'll study Spanish harder,

206
00:14:33,450 --> 00:14:37,910
and rewrite my research proposal.

207
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,500
Okay, don't push yourself too hard.

208
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:42,750
You'll need your health.

209
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:45,200
Otherwise, all will be lost.

210
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:47,410
Okay.

211
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,540
I thought you were asleep.

212
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:31,080
Grandma, can we resume our walks?

213
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,040
No.

214
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:34,870
What if you get pushed again?

215
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:38,790
Can you protect yourself?

216
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,620
Listen to me. The world…

217
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,370
-is full of scary beasts.
-Is full of scary beasts.

218
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:46,450
Yes, I know that.

219
00:16:47,830 --> 00:16:50,250
Then be content to stay home.

220
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:01,370
I envy you. Free to go where you choose.

221
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,950
Nothing will happen from waiting.

222
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:23,750
Hello!

223
00:17:38,660 --> 00:17:42,370
I'll miss the money, but Hayato is right.

224
00:17:49,450 --> 00:17:51,870
Listen, I've come to a decision.

225
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:56,500
I need to quit this job.

226
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:00,790
Are you listening?

227
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,620
Kumiko!

228
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:41,250
Kumiko!

229
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:44,870
What's wrong?

230
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:47,000
Kumiko is missing!

231
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:03,080
Stop!

232
00:19:04,370 --> 00:19:05,870
What are you doing?

233
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:08,200
None of your business!

234
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,290
Let me go!

235
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,160
What, by yourself?

236
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:30,290
-Let's call it a day.
-Take me.

237
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:33,950
Take me to the sea.

238
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:38,160
Or I'll say you
groped my breasts and get you fired.

239
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,290
Do what you want. I'm going home.

240
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:00,450
This will cost extra.

241
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:09,750
280 yen.

242
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:13,250
For the ticket. I've got a railcard.

243
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:15,500
Is something wrong?

244
00:20:15,580 --> 00:20:17,120
No, it's nothing.

245
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:22,910
It's Tsuneo. I've found Kumiko.

246
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:25,500
Excuse me.

247
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:39,160
I'll have her back
as soon as I can. Please understand.

248
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:44,910
-Tiger.
-What?

249
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:46,870
Tigers everywhere.

250
00:20:46,950 --> 00:20:48,160
Tigers?

251
00:20:51,870 --> 00:20:52,830
Hey.

252
00:20:52,910 --> 00:20:53,950
Where to now?

253
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:54,870
Home.

254
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:57,370
What about the sea?

255
00:20:57,950 --> 00:20:59,500
You were so insistent.

256
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:02,500
Watch where you're going!

257
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:05,200
What? She bumped into me.

258
00:21:08,370 --> 00:21:11,410
Are you serious? What a jerk.

259
00:21:12,540 --> 00:21:13,950
Hey, watch it!!

260
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:14,870
Yes, Granny.

261
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:18,040
Mess with me and I'll rip out your heart

262
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,200
and feed it to you!

263
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,040
Sorry!

264
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:32,200
What do you want to do, Ms. Josee?

265
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,700
Are we going or not?

266
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:46,370
Be careful.

267
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:52,450
Not there?

268
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:53,870
No, it's this way.

269
00:21:53,950 --> 00:21:55,120
Really?

270
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,790
Now, where's the elevator?

271
00:21:59,410 --> 00:22:01,370
Why are there so many people?

272
00:22:01,450 --> 00:22:02,790
Beats me.

273
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:14,410
It's not my first time on a train.

274
00:22:16,330 --> 00:22:17,870
Stop staring.

275
00:22:17,950 --> 00:22:22,450
No, I was just wondering
how you see the world.

276
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:27,160
Forests, deserts, New York, Paris…

277
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:30,040
I've never imagined them that way.

278
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,950
The way you drew them.

279
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:35,160
You went into my room?

280
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:38,660
I'd like to see an ocean like that.

281
