my local fish store had one,

562
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:50,410
and I fell in love with it.

563
00:42:51,910 --> 00:42:55,830
I'd go to look at it
every day after school.

564
00:42:57,540 --> 00:43:00,250
When I learned it swam in schools,

565
00:43:00,330 --> 00:43:01,620
my interest grew more.

566
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,290
It wants to be with family too.

567
00:43:07,620 --> 00:43:08,450
What do you mean?

568
00:43:08,950 --> 00:43:10,870
My parents are divorced.

569
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:16,120
Dad left home, and Mom
was always busy working.

570
00:43:17,450 --> 00:43:21,660
I don't think he was sad,
though, the clarion angel.

571
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:25,330
He had you come every day.

572
00:43:28,250 --> 00:43:31,830
I've long dreamed
of seeing him swimming in a school.

573
00:43:33,370 --> 00:43:36,580
It's why I've studied so hard
and saved money.

574
00:43:37,290 --> 00:43:39,080
They're hard to find

575
00:43:39,620 --> 00:43:42,160
so a brief diving vacation wouldn't do.

576
00:43:44,450 --> 00:43:45,580
It's a nice dream.

577
00:43:47,950 --> 00:43:49,370
I hope it comes true.

578
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:56,790
Actually, next year…

579
00:43:58,330 --> 00:43:59,330
This is defective.

580
00:43:59,410 --> 00:44:00,700
That's odd.

581
00:44:04,370 --> 00:44:05,410
There, all fixed.

582
00:44:21,700 --> 00:44:23,790
That hurts!

583
00:44:23,870 --> 00:44:26,410
Why the heck did you do that?

584
00:44:46,540 --> 00:44:47,370
Hello!

585
00:44:54,700 --> 00:44:55,830
Ready to go?

586
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:03,330
Kumiko!

587
00:45:06,540 --> 00:45:09,290
Grandma, the world isn't all scary.

588
00:45:48,250 --> 00:45:49,790
I'm going to have nightmares.

589
00:45:50,370 --> 00:45:53,200
Nightmares? You came to see this.

590
00:45:53,830 --> 00:45:57,790
I wanted to see
the scariest thing here with you.

591
00:46:00,620 --> 00:46:03,200
I thought I could do it
with you by my side.

592
00:46:03,950 --> 00:46:04,830
With me by your side?

593
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:13,950
To hold onto.

594
00:46:16,700 --> 00:46:20,080
I needed something
to hold onto if I got scared.

595
00:46:25,500 --> 00:46:26,580
That hurts.

596
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:35,120
I read a story aloud
to children the other day.

597
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:37,080
You, Josee? What was it?

598
00:46:37,830 --> 00:46:38,950
The Little Mermaid.

599
00:46:39,040 --> 00:46:41,000
Wow, that's amazing.

600
00:46:43,080 --> 00:46:44,410
I didn't read it very well.

601
00:46:45,120 --> 00:46:47,700
I got so nervous, I couldn't look up.

602
00:46:49,620 --> 00:46:50,580
It was scary.

603
00:46:53,290 --> 00:46:55,500
But then I drew a picture,

604
00:46:55,580 --> 00:46:57,160
and the children all loved it.

605
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:02,000
I want to draw more.

606
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:03,500
More?

607
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:07,290
As a job. I want to draw professionally.

608
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:10,830
I want to give it a shot.

609
00:47:11,830 --> 00:47:12,950
Like what you're doing.

610
00:47:16,660 --> 00:47:18,160
Well, I love…

611
00:47:19,290 --> 00:47:20,120
your drawings.

612
00:47:22,330 --> 00:47:24,250
Pretty cocky for a servant.

613
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:30,500
Cherry blossoms fall
like rain here in spring.

614
00:47:31,120 --> 00:47:33,120
My dad used to bring me.

615
00:47:34,450 --> 00:47:35,830
It must be beautiful.

616
00:47:37,080 --> 00:47:41,080
If you want to see it,
you can bring me next year.

617
00:47:43,580 --> 00:47:44,410
What's wrong?

618
00:47:46,870 --> 00:47:47,700
Nothing.

619
00:48:20,910 --> 00:48:23,750
Did you hear about Ms. Yamamura?

620
00:48:23,830 --> 00:48:27,160
She's had a bad heart for some time.

621
00:48:28,040 --> 00:48:30,160
And she was quite old.

622
00:48:30,250 --> 00:48:33,250
CHIZU YAMAMURA

623
00:48:41,830 --> 00:48:43,370
The morticians left.

624
00:48:45,910 --> 00:48:47,950
If you need to talk, I'm here.

625
00:48:49,200 --> 00:48:50,660
About what to do next.

626
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:58,120
Grandma left me a little money to live on.

627
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:00,700
I'll be okay for a while.

628
00:49:02,160 --> 00:49:03,000
I see.

629
00:49:04,830 --> 00:49:07,080
But I can't afford to pay.

630
00:49:09,080 --> 00:49:12,410
I can't pay My Servant wages.

631
00:49:17,410 --> 00:49:18,250
I understand.

632
00:50:06,370 --> 00:50:08,750
OUT OF OXYGEN

633
00:50:35,290 --> 00:50:38,200
It's rare for you
to lose track of oxygen, Tsuneo.

634
00:50:39,290 --> 00:50:41,330
You seem distracted.

635
00:50:41,410 --> 00:50:43,750
I know. You confessed--

636
00:50:46,120 --> 00:50:48,160
Josee's grandmother died.

637
00:50:49,950 --> 00:50:52,910
So now she's all alone.

638
00:50:53,750 --> 00:50:55,450
That's pretty harsh.

639
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:57,950
And worrying.

640
00:51:00,370 --> 00:51:02,580
She's not a child,

641
00:51:03,080 --> 00:51:05,620
and there are welfare services
and facilities.

642
00:51:10,830 --> 00:51:12,540
"Free yourself from life."

643
00:51:13,500 --> 00:51:16,200
"From that which others call life."

644
00:51:16,750 --> 00:51:17,790
"Be free from emotion,

645
00:51:18,500 --> 00:51:22,040
from one's strengths,
one's own weaknesses."

646
00:51:22,620 --> 00:51:24,790
"Be but one momentary breath,

647
00:51:24,870 --> 00:51:28,700
one-millionth of a billion nebulas."

648
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:38,040
Are you home, Ms. Kumiko? It's Mizushima.

649
00:51:42,330 --> 00:51:45,040
This is Mr. Fujita, a social worker.

650
00:51:45,790 --> 00:51:51,750
The resident's association chairman
got a call from one of your neighbors.

651
00:51:52,330 --> 00:51:55,000
They heard your grandmother passed

652
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:57,080
and felt you needed assistance.

653
00:51:58,450 --> 00:51:59,660
It's none of their business.

654
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:05,290
How do you plan to move forward?

655
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:07,830
Pictures.

656
00:52:09,910 --> 00:52:12,080
I plan to draw pictures.

657
00:52:14,910 --> 00:52:19,700
You're saying you'll earn
a living as an artist?

658
00:52:20,660 --> 00:52:23,950
I think it's wonderful to have a dream.

659
00:52:24,540 --> 00:52:28,290
Dreams are one thing. Reality is another.

660
00:52:28,370 --> 00:52:30,910
You of all should know that.

661
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:34,620
Don't be foolish. Go look for work…

662
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:39,040
Your grandma's not here to dote on you.

663
00:52:40,160 --> 00:52:41,700
Mr. Fujita.

664
00:52:41,790 --> 00:52:47,120
Or is there someone else
who will support you?

665
00:53:08,500 --> 00:53:09,750
Are you okay?

666
00:53:12,620 --> 00:53:14,790
I'm Mai. We met the other day.

667
00:53:16,750 --> 00:53:17,580
Why are you here?

668
00:53:18,620 --> 00:53:23,250
I remembered Tsuneo saying
you lived by the river.

669
00:53:24,750 --> 00:53:29,160
It would've been faster
if we had just asked Tsuneo.

670
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:34,040
What do you want?

671
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:41,910
I beg you to free Tsuneo.

672
00:53:42,870 --> 00:53:45,200
Wait, we came to cheer her up!

673
00:53:45,290 --> 00:53:48,410
He's worked so hard for his dream.

674
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:52,910
Studying Spanish, working to save money

675
00:53:53,410 --> 00:53:55,040
so he can study abroad.

676
00:53:55,620 --> 00:53:56,450
Study abroad?

677
00:53:57,080 --> 00:54:00,620
Next March, he's going to Mexico.

678
00:54:02,580 --> 00:54:03,580
He didn't tell you?

679
00:54:05,660 --> 00:54:07,950
Would you support his dream?

680
00:54:08,580 --> 00:54:09,620
At this rate--

681
00:54:09,700 --> 00:54:12,120
Why do you have to ask my permission?

682
00:54:14,290 --> 00:54:16,200
What's your relationship with him?

683
00:54:28,370 --> 00:54:29,290
It's sympathy.

684
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:34,500
Tsuneo only visits you
out of pity for your condition.

685
00:54:35,540 --> 00:54:36,750
What the hell are you saying?

686
00:54:37,870 --> 00:54:38,790
Don't listen to her.

687
00:54:40,500 --> 00:54:42,160
Hey, wait up!

688
00:54:44,500 --> 00:54:46,500
What types of cytoplasm do I mean?

689
00:54:46,580 --> 00:54:49,040
That's right, cytoplasmic genomes.

690
00:54:49,830 --> 00:54:53,700
You can consider them
a place to store genomes.

691
00:55:00,200 --> 00:55:02,540
THE LITTLE MERMAID

692
00:55:09,080 --> 00:55:09,950
Hello.

693
00:55:17,580 --> 00:55:20,750
Josee, I brought fish-shaped cakes.

694
00:55:23,500 --> 00:55:24,540
Why did you come?

695
00:55:27,910 --> 00:55:28,750
Josee?

696
00:55:30,660 --> 00:55:31,500
Your room…

697
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:37,790
I asked a helper to come
and clean the place once a month.

698
00:55:38,540 --> 00:55:39,620
And your pictures?

699
00:55:39,700 --> 00:55:40,540
Thrown out.

700
00:55:40,620 --> 00:55:41,830
What? Why?

701
00:55:42,540 --> 00:55:44,410
None of your business.

702
00:55:45,370 --> 00:55:47,410
If that's all, you can go.

703
00:56:02,660 --> 00:56:03,790
I'll fix it right away.

704
00:56:13,330 --> 00:56:14,450
I want to go to the sea.

705
00:56:17,330 --> 00:56:19,950
This will be your last job as My Servant.

706
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:00,330
Up to the waterline?

707
00:57:00,830 --> 00:57:01,750
This is fine.

708
00:57:03,870 --> 00:57:05,120
How about a warm drink?

709
00:57:05,620 --> 00:57:06,450
No thanks.

710
00:57:18,580 --> 00:57:19,410
It's salty.

711
00:57:24,370 --> 00:57:25,200
Josee.

712
00:57:31,410 --> 00:57:34,830
I don't want money.
Don't call this the last job.

713
00:57:35,620 --> 00:57:36,450
Josee!

714
00:57:38,450 --> 00:57:39,410
I'm no longer Josee.

715
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:44,330
I've taken a job in an office.

716
00:57:45,250 --> 00:57:47,950
You didn't need to get rid of your art.

717
00:57:48,540 --> 00:57:49,750
It was out of reach.

718
00:57:51,330 --> 00:57:52,700
Everything's always out of reach.

719
00:57:54,080 --> 00:57:56,160
The red balloon caught on the roof.

720
00:57:57,040 --> 00:57:58,910
The cicada husk on the tree.

721
00:58:00,290 --> 00:58:02,750
Walking under an umbrella in the rain.

722
00:58:03,250 --> 00:58:05,950
Climbing the steps of a shrine.

723
00:58:07,290 --> 00:58:08,120
All of it.

724
00:58:10,580 --> 00:58:13,450
I no longer wish to reach for any of it.

725
00:58:15,330 --> 00:58:19,450
If you really don't,
then why do you look so sad?

726
00:58:21,620 --> 00:58:23,160
Don't give up what you love!

727
00:58:26,620 --> 00:58:28,120
You're leaving soon, right?

728
00:58:35,250 --> 00:58:36,700
The healthy wouldn't understand.

729
00:59:12,000 --> 00:59:13,120
Josee!

730
00:59:17,620 --> 00:59:19,000
Josee!

731
00:59:38,620 --> 00:59:39,450
My Servant…

732
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:42,040
My Servant.

733
00:59:44,700 --> 00:59:45,830
My Servant!

734
00:59:46,870 --> 00:59:48,080
My Servant!

735
00:59:50,830 --> 00:59:54,370
Tsuneo!

736
01:00:01,120 --> 01:00:02,410
Are you all right?

737
01:00:03,620 --> 01:00:07,910
There's been a traffic accident!

738
01:00:17,660 --> 01:00:19,120
-Remove the scoop.
-Yes.

739
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:20,160
Cutting away clothes.

740
01:00:20,250 --> 01:00:24,250
Pulse 120, BP 70 over 40, saturation 94%.

741
01:00:24,330 --> 01:00:26,330
Maintain ten liters of oxygen.

742
01:00:26,410 --> 01:00:27,750
-Peripheral off?
-Not yet.

743
01:00:27,830 --> 01:00:29,870
Quickly, 18-gauge, full throttle.

744
01:00:29,950 --> 01:00:33,870
-Crossmatch. Don't forget the blood gas.
-Got it.

745
01:00:33,950 --> 01:00:35,500
X-ray standby!

746
01:00:36,120 --> 01:00:38,080
Airways clear, respiration's steady.

747
01:00:38,160 --> 01:00:39,830
Starting echo.

748
01:00:39,910 --> 01:00:41,450
Negative. Pneumothorax is fine.

749
01:00:42,700 --> 01:00:43,540
Mr. Suzukawa?

750
01:00:43,620 --> 01:00:47,370
Mr. Tsuneo Suzukawa? Can you hear me?

751
01:00:47,450 --> 01:00:50,700
If you can hear me, open your eyes.

752
01:01:13,620 --> 01:01:14,540
Are you awake?

753
01:01:15,620 --> 01:01:16,790
Yes.

754
01:01:16,870 --> 01:01:19,660
You were in a traffic accident.
This is a hospital.

755
01:01:21,160 --> 01:01:22,370
I'll call the doctor.

756
01:01:25,290 --> 01:01:27,830
The girl in the wheelchair?

757
01:01:27,910 --> 01:01:31,450
Oh, yes, we asked her to go home today.

758
01:01:31,540 --> 01:01:34,620
She insisted on waiting till you awoke.

759
01:01:35,330 --> 01:01:37,290
So she's not injured?

760
01:01:37,370 --> 01:01:38,200
No.

761
01:01:41,250 --> 01:01:42,620
How do you feel?

762
01:01:43,410 --> 01:01:45,250
I was in an accident?

763
01:01:46,040 --> 01:01:48,080
You suffered a concussion,

764
01:01:48,160 --> 01:01:50,620
but tests showed nothing was wrong.

765
01:01:51,250 --> 01:01:54,080
Your internal organs are sound,

766
01:01:55,080 --> 01:01:58,580
but your right shinbone
is broken at the ankle.

767
01:01:59,830 --> 01:02:01,330
In short, an open fracture.

768
01:02:02,120 --> 01:02:04,250
Emergency surgery was done

769
01:02:04,330 --> 01:02:06,790
to prevent infection at the wound.

770
01:02:07,330 --> 01:02:10,950
We secured the fracture
with screws and a plate.

771
01:02:11,580 --> 01:02:16,450
It'll take two months
before it can bear your weight.

772
01:02:17,120 --> 01:02:18,250
Two months.

773
01:02:19,040 --> 01:02:20,330
One more thing.

774
01:02:20,410 --> 01:02:26,080
Surgery couldn't unite
the joint surfaces perfectly.

775
01:02:26,160 --> 01:02:28,580
There's a risk of osteoarthritis.

776
01:02:29,500 --> 01:02:31,450
Osteoarthritis?

777
01:02:32,540 --> 01:02:37,080
You could experience
joint pain and stiffness,

778
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:40,160
making it hard to walk or run like before.

779
01:02:41,370 --> 01:02:44,080
The hairline fracture in your left arm

780
01:02:44,160 --> 01:02:48,410
may make crutches moot for a while.

781
01:02:50,910 --> 01:02:51,950
Will I heal?

782
01:02:54,500 --> 01:02:56,870
It's hard to say at this stage.

783
01:03:11,830 --> 01:03:12,660
Josee.

784
01:03:13,830 --> 01:03:14,870
I'm sorry.

785
01:03:18,540 --> 01:03:19,620
It's not your fault.

786
01:03:22,370 --> 01:03:24,870
I seem to be in pretty bad shape.

787
01:03:25,910 --> 01:03:28,620
Even rehab might not fix everything.

788
01:03:31,580 --> 01:03:35,080
If it turns out I can't walk again, I…

789
01:03:43,160 --> 01:03:44,120
I need to sleep.

790
01:04:01,160 --> 01:04:02,000
Quiet!

791
01:04:16,790 --> 01:04:18,870
You don't need to come, Mom.

792
01:04:19,370 --> 01:04:20,950
You'll hurt your back.

793
01:04:21,620 --> 01:04:23,500
It's no big deal, I swear.

794
01:04:24,750 --> 01:04:29,250
I'll come visit
after I leave the hospital. See you.

795
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:33,330
Professor.

796
01:04:35,620 --> 01:04:37,410
How are you, Tsuneo?

797
01:04:38,000 --> 01:04:40,450
I'm sorry to worry you.

798
01:04:43,500 --> 01:04:45,910
Listen, about your study abroad.

799
01:04:47,330 --> 01:04:49,790
They'd like another student

800
01:04:49,870 --> 01:04:52,370
to come in March if you can't.

801
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:57,910
It's a pity,
but you'll get another chance.

802
01:04:58,620 --> 01:05:01,910
For now, just focus on getting well.

803
01:05:06,660 --> 01:05:07,660
That's not the problem.

804
01:05:09,500 --> 01:05:12,910
It's possible I may not
be able to dive anymore.

805
01:05:15,330 --> 01:05:20,120
If I can't do that,
I'll lose my reason for going abroad.

806
01:05:30,450 --> 01:05:34,000
SPANISH GRAMMAR

807
01:06:01,790 --> 01:06:03,750
So rotate your ankle

808
01:06:03,830 --> 01:06:08,080
and extend your toes
to the extent possible.

809
01:06:08,700 --> 01:06:11,540
When the swelling goes down,

810
01:06:11,620 --> 01:06:15,290
we can shift to your rehabilitation.

811
01:06:17,950 --> 01:06:18,790
Tsuneo.

812
01:06:20,700 --> 01:06:21,830
I bought pudding.

813
01:06:23,830 --> 01:06:24,700
Thanks.

814
01:06:27,000 --> 01:06:28,700
Starting rehab already?

815
01:06:29,910 --> 01:06:30,750
Yeah.

816
01:06:31,540 --> 01:06:33,330
I'll put this in the fridge.

817
01:06:35,120 --> 01:06:40,000
My parents keep sending
rice and vegetables.

818
01:06:40,080 --> 01:06:42,410
My fridge is bulging.

819
01:06:42,500 --> 01:06:44,250
SPANISH GRAMMAR

820
01:06:50,580 --> 01:06:52,870
Want to get some fresh air?

821
01:07:05,500 --> 01:07:07,620
Feel free to say what's on your mind.

822
01:07:08,950 --> 01:07:10,620
I'm here to give you my support.

823
01:07:13,410 --> 01:07:17,870
It doesn't matter anymore…
Studying abroad, Mexico.

824
01:07:20,040 --> 01:07:23,540
I thought I was stronger than this.

825
01:07:24,910 --> 01:07:26,540
Please don't give up.

826
01:07:26,620 --> 01:07:28,040
Work hard on rehab--

827
01:07:28,120 --> 01:07:30,830
"Work hard"? What if it doesn't matter?

828
01:07:33,330 --> 01:07:35,950
I didn't understand anything.

829
01:07:37,370 --> 01:07:41,080
How scary it is
to reach for something I want.

830
01:07:47,790 --> 01:07:50,080
I…

831
01:07:50,160 --> 01:07:51,080
have feelings for you, Tsuneo!

832
01:07:52,370 --> 01:07:54,750
I just didn't want that

833
01:07:54,830 --> 01:07:57,870
to get in the way of your goals.

834
01:08:00,120 --> 01:08:01,330
But I can't help it.

835
01:08:03,330 --> 01:08:05,370
I'm madly in love with you!

836
01:08:12,370 --> 01:08:13,750
How'd this happen?

837
01:08:15,750 --> 01:08:17,620
Mai, listen. I--

838
01:08:17,700 --> 01:08:18,830
I know.

839
01:08:20,250 --> 01:08:22,950
I don't need a "Sorry" or a "Thanks."

840
01:08:23,750 --> 01:08:26,910
I hate women who cry in front of men.

841
01:08:30,750 --> 01:08:31,660
But…

842
01:08:34,160 --> 01:08:35,450
I needed to say it.

843
01:08:44,660 --> 01:08:46,250
We should get back.

844
01:09:06,910 --> 01:09:09,290
I know you're there! Answer the door!

845
01:09:14,370 --> 01:09:15,370
If you don't…

846
01:09:17,450 --> 01:09:18,290
Go away!

847
01:09:20,410 --> 01:09:21,370
Don't come back.

848
01:09:24,370 --> 01:09:26,830
Tsuneo's given up on studying abroad.

849
01:09:28,830 --> 01:09:30,660
So now I'm making him mine.

850
01:09:31,580 --> 01:09:35,790
I'll give him the love
he needs to forget the sea.

851
01:09:37,950 --> 01:09:40,660
I never wanted him to go to Mexico.

852
01:09:42,290 --> 01:09:44,540
I prayed he'd forget his silly dream

853
01:09:45,660 --> 01:09:49,750
and stay near me.
I wanted to be by his side.

854
01:09:52,200 --> 01:09:54,160
I know him so much better than you.

855
01:09:55,200 --> 01:09:59,580
His love for talking about fish,
the awful way he hums.

856
01:10:00,500 --> 01:10:02,330
He's bad at rock-paper-scissors.

857
01:10:03,700 --> 01:10:06,950
He likes pudding, hates cucumbers,

858
01:10:07,040 --> 01:10:09,790
and always has ice-cold hands.

859
01:10:12,120 --> 01:10:14,910
I could name a hundred more things.

860
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:17,700
I know him far better.

861
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:21,910
Well, say something!

862
01:10:23,790 --> 01:10:25,830
My Servant's never giving up.

863
01:10:26,410 --> 01:10:30,700
He'll never forget
about fish or abandon his dream!

864
01:10:31,290 --> 01:10:32,450
That's who he is!

865
01:10:33,410 --> 01:10:35,040
You know that, right?

866
01:10:37,290 --> 01:10:40,660
I can't name a hundred things about him.

867
01:10:42,750 --> 01:10:45,290
But you can't beat my feelings for him.

868
01:10:47,580 --> 01:10:49,870
If that's true, then show it!

869
01:11:05,250 --> 01:11:06,330
Salty.

870
01:11:15,830 --> 01:11:17,250
You're clumsy.

871
01:11:18,830 --> 01:11:20,410
I'm a good woman.

872
01:11:25,620 --> 01:11:29,290
Why don't you buy me dinner then?

873
01:11:29,370 --> 01:11:30,200
What?

874
01:12:06,160 --> 01:12:07,000
Josee.

875
01:12:09,950 --> 01:12:11,080
I have a request.

876
01:12:22,870 --> 01:12:26,910
You should let the characters
show more emotions.

877
01:12:27,580 --> 01:12:29,040
Say how they feel.

878
01:12:29,950 --> 01:12:30,790
I see.

879
01:13:08,160 --> 01:13:09,200
Hey, redhead.

880
01:13:10,330 --> 01:13:11,250
Josee?

881
01:13:12,950 --> 01:13:13,870
Lend me your face.

882
01:13:15,080 --> 01:13:16,120
What?

883
01:13:16,200 --> 01:13:19,410
LOST PROFILE

884
01:13:20,540 --> 01:13:24,910
I desired nothing but my escape from him.

885
01:13:25,700 --> 01:13:26,830
That is all.

886
01:13:28,330 --> 01:13:32,120
Upon reflection,
it was truly a pitiful story.

887
01:13:40,830 --> 01:13:41,700
It's done.

888
01:13:42,290 --> 01:13:43,120
Ta-da.

889
01:13:46,870 --> 01:13:48,080
What's this?

890
01:13:48,160 --> 01:13:50,750
Isn't it obvious? Permission to leave.

891
01:13:51,750 --> 01:13:53,790
No, why do you have it?

892
01:13:53,870 --> 01:13:56,200
I just figured you might seek

893
01:13:56,290 --> 01:13:58,910
a change of pace once in a while.

894
01:14:01,290 --> 01:14:04,160
I'm sorry, but I'm not in the mood.

895
01:14:04,250 --> 01:14:08,500
Don't be such a bore, Tsuneo.
Let's have some fun!

896
01:14:08,580 --> 01:14:09,750
Leave me alone!

897
01:14:15,870 --> 01:14:19,790
As your diving buddy,
it's my job to give you oxygen…

898
01:14:21,870 --> 01:14:25,700
whenever you need it.
So shut up and follow me.

899
01:14:32,910 --> 01:14:34,160
What's going on?

900
01:14:34,250 --> 01:14:35,330
Don't ask questions.

901
01:14:40,290 --> 01:14:41,120
This place.

902
01:14:59,660 --> 01:15:04,040
THE MERMAID AND THE SHINY WING

903
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:09,160
The Mermaid and the Shiny Wing.

904
01:15:18,870 --> 01:15:21,200
From the floor of the deep blue sea,

905
01:15:21,290 --> 01:15:23,500
festive music is heard.

906
01:15:24,160 --> 01:15:26,750
It's a mermaid's 20th birthday

907
01:15:26,830 --> 01:15:30,080
when she can leave the sea.

908
01:15:34,950 --> 01:15:35,830
You're doing fine.

909
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:47,830
The mermaid received
a magic shell as a gift.

910
01:15:48,950 --> 01:15:50,330
And it spoke to her.

911
01:15:50,910 --> 01:15:53,910
"You can use me to turn human,

912
01:15:54,000 --> 01:15:55,830
and back into a mermaid again."

913
01:15:57,000 --> 01:16:00,660
"But you must not wish for anything else."

914
01:16:01,330 --> 01:16:03,160
"For if you do,

915
01:16:04,660 --> 01:16:07,250
you'll turn to froth and vanish forever."

916
01:16:08,830 --> 01:16:12,660
"I understand,"
said the mermaid and swam ashore.

917
01:16:14,040 --> 01:16:17,200
"Oh, shell, turn me into a human."

918
01:16:19,160 --> 01:16:22,410
Suddenly, her fins became graceful legs.

919
01:16:23,410 --> 01:16:27,410
"How wonderful,"
she exclaimed as she climbed a hill.

920
01:16:28,500 --> 01:16:31,580
But the world outside was full of danger.

921
01:16:33,160 --> 01:16:36,410
A ferocious tiger appeared before her.

922
01:16:38,040 --> 01:16:40,080
The mermaid tried to run

923
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:43,250
but lost her footing and fell.

924
01:16:44,330 --> 01:16:48,580
Clinging to a rock, she yelled, "Help!"

925
01:16:50,290 --> 01:16:54,120
Just then, a young man
with pure white wings

926
01:16:54,200 --> 01:16:56,910
descended from the sky to help.

927
01:16:57,910 --> 01:17:00,120
"Thank you. Those are lovely wings."

928
01:17:01,040 --> 01:17:04,250
The young man
beamed happily at those words.

929
01:17:05,450 --> 01:17:08,790
"When spring comes,
I'm taking flight with them."

930
01:17:09,830 --> 01:17:11,910
For he had a dream.

931
01:17:13,870 --> 01:17:18,410
It was to fly
to a shiny sea far, far away.

932
01:17:19,330 --> 01:17:23,040
A place where a family
of bright orange fish swam.

933
01:17:23,790 --> 01:17:25,910
A vast sea, full of fun and frolic.

934
01:17:27,410 --> 01:17:31,450
The two became friends
and went to many places together.

935
01:17:32,830 --> 01:17:36,370
"Every place makes my heart
dance with such joy,

936
01:17:36,450 --> 01:17:38,040
I feel like skipping."

937
01:17:39,040 --> 01:17:42,330
The mermaid saw her world grow and expand.

938
01:17:43,790 --> 01:17:46,370
The seasons changed and spring arrived.

939
01:17:47,250 --> 01:17:51,080
The day for
the young man's departure came.

940
01:17:51,790 --> 01:17:56,580
The mermaid was sad
and walked alone in the woods.

941
01:17:57,450 --> 01:18:01,700
Again, a ferocious tiger
appeared before her.

942
01:18:02,660 --> 01:18:06,290
Claws sharp, fangs bared,
it pounced on the mermaid.

943
01:18:06,870 --> 01:18:09,200
"Look out," cried the young man,

944
01:18:09,290 --> 01:18:12,000
appearing just in time to save her.

945
01:18:12,870 --> 01:18:15,700
But this time, he was injured,

946
01:18:16,330 --> 01:18:18,870
his gorgeous wings, broken.

947
01:18:20,410 --> 01:18:22,450
Sobbing with grief,

948
01:18:22,950 --> 01:18:26,450
the mermaid took
the magic shell in her hands

949
01:18:27,790 --> 01:18:30,540
and wished, "Please save him."

950
01:18:32,330 --> 01:18:35,250
Within seconds, his wounds healed

951
01:18:35,790 --> 01:18:37,540
and the youth awoke alive and well,

952
01:18:38,410 --> 01:18:41,660
but his wings would never return.

953
01:18:42,830 --> 01:18:48,450
"I can no longer reach
the shiny sea," he lamented.

954
01:18:49,160 --> 01:18:50,830
The mermaid said, "Raise your head."

955
01:18:51,870 --> 01:18:55,330
"You have larger wings in your heart."

956
01:18:56,750 --> 01:18:59,250
"With those wings, you sheltered me

957
01:19:00,080 --> 01:19:02,700
and used them to push me forward."

958
01:19:03,580 --> 01:19:07,700
"With wings of the heart,
you can fly anywhere."

959
01:19:09,250 --> 01:19:12,870
The young man set off
for the shiny sea by boat.

960
01:19:14,040 --> 01:19:16,620
In driving rain or stormy winds,

961
01:19:16,700 --> 01:19:18,790
he pushed ever forward.

962
01:19:19,580 --> 01:19:23,540
"I'm not afraid
for I'm in pursuit of my dreams."

963
01:19:24,540 --> 01:19:30,290
His heart wings were
strong, supple, and beautiful.

964
01:19:30,370 --> 01:19:32,160
And most of all, unbreakable.

965
01:19:33,330 --> 01:19:35,750
At last, he found the shiny sea.

966
01:19:37,040 --> 01:19:39,700
With great joy, he dove into it.

967
01:19:39,790 --> 01:19:44,080
He started swimming freely
with the orange fish,

968
01:19:45,330 --> 01:19:48,450
so happy that his dream came true.

969
01:19:49,910 --> 01:19:53,910
"Oh, shell, you can now
turn me into bubbles."

970
01:19:55,700 --> 01:19:59,410
But her legs turned back into fins

971
01:19:59,500 --> 01:20:02,040
and nothing else occurred.

972
01:20:03,410 --> 01:20:05,000
The magic shell spoke.

973
01:20:06,040 --> 01:20:07,330
"Wishing for another's benefit

974
01:20:07,870 --> 01:20:12,080
and not your own
will never make you vanish."

975
01:20:15,200 --> 01:20:19,790
So with a heart filled
with shiny jewels of memories,

976
01:20:19,870 --> 01:20:23,160
the mermaid returned to the deep blue sea.

977
01:20:24,700 --> 01:20:25,540
The end.

978
01:22:13,410 --> 01:22:14,700
Why are you hiding?

979
01:22:22,580 --> 01:22:24,040
Look, I think he can make it!

980
01:22:40,410 --> 01:22:42,450
-You did it!
-You did it!

981
01:22:54,200 --> 01:22:56,830
Yukichi, My Servant walked today.

982
01:23:00,450 --> 01:23:02,500
Stray cats must not get spoiled.

983
01:23:10,580 --> 01:23:11,830
Must not get spoiled.

984
01:23:14,500 --> 01:23:16,330
Fight the tiger yourself.

985
01:23:20,370 --> 01:23:21,450
I'm getting out!

986
01:23:23,160 --> 01:23:26,200
I just need to make weekly visits.

987
01:23:27,000 --> 01:23:30,700
That's great. Congrats!

988
01:23:32,120 --> 01:23:32,950
Thanks.

989
01:23:35,660 --> 01:23:38,000
I'm not sure about the side effects yet,

990
01:23:39,200 --> 01:23:42,040
but I'm going to Mexico no matter what.

991
01:23:44,040 --> 01:23:46,120
Now that I've got heart wings.

992
01:23:50,660 --> 01:23:52,120
You'll be fine.

993
01:23:55,790 --> 01:23:58,790
They're letting me leave on the 24th.

994
01:23:59,950 --> 01:24:02,330
Can you come get me?

995
01:24:02,910 --> 01:24:03,870
10 a.m.

996
01:24:08,750 --> 01:24:09,580
Josee?

997
01:24:12,540 --> 01:24:14,620
I'm just so happy.

998
01:24:16,580 --> 01:24:17,410
Thank you.

999
01:25:42,580 --> 01:25:43,410
Josee?

1000
01:25:58,410 --> 01:25:59,370
Josee!

1001
01:26:22,700 --> 01:26:23,540
Josee.

1002
01:26:25,250 --> 01:26:26,080
Here.

1003
01:26:31,250 --> 01:26:32,080
Ms. Kana!

1004
01:26:32,580 --> 01:26:35,250
Tsuneo, congrats on getting out.

1005
01:26:36,080 --> 01:26:37,040
Where's Josee?

1006
01:26:37,120 --> 01:26:38,750
I haven't seen her today.

1007
01:26:41,000 --> 01:26:41,830
Sorry.

1008
01:26:43,080 --> 01:26:44,540
You're so right.

1009
01:26:46,580 --> 01:26:48,500
Big trouble! Josee's missing!

1010
01:27:16,290 --> 01:27:19,200
A girl in a wheelchair just boarded.

1011
01:27:20,790 --> 01:27:22,750
Do you know where to?

1012
01:28:19,700 --> 01:28:21,660
Attention, guests.

1013
01:28:23,040 --> 01:28:25,750
The zoo will be closing in a few minutes.

1014
01:28:26,660 --> 01:28:32,580
Please make sure you have
all your belongings with you.

1015
01:29:31,620 --> 01:29:32,500
Josee.

1016
01:29:49,160 --> 01:29:50,000
Stop!

1017
01:29:52,290 --> 01:29:53,120
Sorry!

1018
01:30:10,950 --> 01:30:12,040
Josee!

1019
01:30:25,950 --> 01:30:27,040
That hurts.

1020
01:30:29,830 --> 01:30:32,120
You all right, Josee?

1021
01:30:33,330 --> 01:30:34,910
Are you okay yourself?

1022
01:30:39,040 --> 01:30:39,870
Your leg.

1023
01:30:40,790 --> 01:30:42,410
You just got out.

1024
01:30:44,080 --> 01:30:47,950
In my panic to find you,
I found myself running.

1025
01:30:49,290 --> 01:30:50,120
De ce?

1026
01:30:55,500 --> 01:30:57,870
I've decided to try to become

1027
01:30:57,950 --> 01:30:59,870
a picture book illustrator.

1028
01:31:01,080 --> 01:31:02,910
I plan to stand on my own two feet.

1029
01:31:05,200 --> 01:31:09,660
You've pushed me
from behind for long enough.

1030
01:31:09,750 --> 01:31:10,790
It's not for you.

1031
01:31:13,330 --> 01:31:14,660
It wasn't for you.

1032
01:31:16,410 --> 01:31:18,250
I want to be Your Servant.

1033
01:31:21,330 --> 01:31:23,540
What about the clarion angel?

1034
01:31:24,120 --> 01:31:26,080
And going to Mexico?

1035
01:31:26,620 --> 01:31:28,620
I'll still go, but…

1036
01:31:30,120 --> 01:31:31,160
Te iubesc, Josee!

1037
01:31:40,290 --> 01:31:41,120
Și...

1038
01:31:43,200 --> 01:31:44,040
Și...

1039
01:31:47,660 --> 01:31:49,200
Și eu te iubesc, servitorul meu.

1040
01:32:17,290 --> 01:32:19,330
Nu este deloc cum mi-am imaginat.

1041
01:32:20,950 --> 01:32:23,330
Ce? Într-un mod rău?

1042
01:32:25,870 --> 01:32:27,160
Într-un mod bun.

1043
01:37:17,790 --> 01:37:19,370
Da.
Drăguț, nu-i așa?

1044
01:37:24,160 --> 01:37:25,870
Chiar pare a fi o ploaie de flori de cireși.

1045
01:37:32,330 --> 01:37:33,700
Ai murit?

1046
01:37:34,370 --> 01:37:35,250
Ce?

1047
01:37:35,330 --> 01:37:36,620
Ești o fantomă?

1048
01:37:37,330 --> 01:37:39,120
Am venit acasă din moment ce e vacanța de primăvară.

1049
01:37:39,200 --> 01:37:40,290
Nu mi-ai spus!

1050
01:37:41,200 --> 01:37:43,370
Voiam să te surprind.

1051
01:37:46,950 --> 01:37:48,660
Destul de îndrăzneț pentru un servitor.

